import React from 'react'; import 'bootstrap/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css'; import './components.css'; const about = () => { return (

ABOUT

I am a Certified Salesforce Developer and Administrator with a background in computer programming and web development. I truly love learning new skills and applying them to create new and exciting applications. I built this React.js website to keep a record of my journey and to use as a portfolio for future projects.

I was born in Dallas and raised in nearby Coppell, TX. After graduating high school I moved to Austin, TX to attend the University of Texas. I had always had a passion for history, and felt that teaching was such a rewarding career. I was admitted to the UTeach program and graduated with a Bacherlor's in History and a Certification to teach K-8 Social Studies. I substitute taught for Pflugerville ISD, the same district I had student taught for, and really enjoyed my time there, but eventually decided I wanted to focus on my passion for music while I was still relatively young.

Serving tables allowed me to focus on writing and recording music, playing shows locally, and eventually going on tour. I actually discovered my passion for programming and web development through this endeavor. I have always loved teaching myself new things, and started to experiments with graphic design so that I could create designs for shirts, record covers, logos, etc. This would eventually lead me to dabbling in HTML and CSS.

I decided that I really wanted to learn more, and began taking courses at Austin Community College. I completed coursework in computer programming, graphic design, database programming, and web development. The more I learned, the more I fell in love with the material. I love the challenge of working on a complex project. I also love pushing myself and acquiring new skills. I am very excited to begin my career in the field.


) } export default about
